vscode-serial-monitor.customBaudRates: Specify the custom baud rates that you'd like to use
vscode-serial-monitor.dataBits: Specify the data bits setting of the Serial Monitor

vscode-serial-monitor.loggingVerbosity: Specify the logging verbosity of the Serial Monitor
vscode-serial-monitor.parity: Specify the parity setting of the Serial Monitor
vscode-serial-monitor.stopBits: Specify the stop bits setting of the Serial Monitor

vscode-serial-monitor.outputFontSize: Specify the font size (points) for the output
vscode-serial-monitor.timestampFormat: Specify a custom format timestamp to be used. You can find the list of all available placeholders here: aka.ms/timestampformats.
vscode-serial-monitor.timestampSeparator: Specify a custom timestamp separator to be used to separate the timestamp from the content. The default will be ' -> '.
